<section class="section wrap" id="faq">
  <div class="section-head text-center">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">// faq</p>
    <h2>questions, answered.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="seo-faq-list">
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>What is think mode in ChatGPT?</summary>
      <p>Think mode (also called extended thinking or reasoning mode) is a built-in feature in ChatGPT that allows the AI model to spend more time reasoning through complex problems before responding. When think mode is enabled, ChatGPT uses deeper chain-of-thought processing to produce more accurate, nuanced, and thorough answers — especially for coding, math, logic, and detailed analysis tasks.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>How do I enable think mode in ChatGPT automatically?</summary>
      <p>Install the ThinkMode+ browser extension for Chrome or Edge. Once installed, ThinkMode+ automatically detects when you open a new chat on ChatGPT and enables think mode for you — instantly and silently. You never have to click the thinking toggle again. It works in the background with zero prompt edits.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>Does ThinkMode+ work with Claude extended thinking?</summary>
      <p>Yes. ThinkMode+ fully supports Claude's extended thinking feature on claude.ai. When you open a new conversation, ThinkMode+ automatically enables extended thinking so Claude uses its deepest reasoning capabilities from the very first message. You can enable or disable Claude support independently.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>Does ThinkMode+ work with Gemini Deep Think?</summary>
      <p>Yes. ThinkMode+ supports Gemini's deep think mode on gemini.google.com. The extension automatically activates Gemini's extended reasoning every time you start a new chat, ensuring you always get Gemini's most thorough responses.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>Is ThinkMode+ free?</summary>
      <p>ThinkMode+ offers a free tier that lets you auto-enable thinking mode on one platform with limited daily activations. For unlimited use across ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini, the Pro plan costs $2.99/month (or $19.99/year). A Pro Squad plan at $4.99/month (or $29.99/year) supports up to 5 devices.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>What is extended thinking in AI?</summary>
      <p>Extended thinking is a feature in modern AI models like ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini that allows the model to perform deeper reasoning before generating a response. Instead of producing an immediate answer, the AI takes additional time to think through the problem step by step, resulting in more accurate and comprehensive outputs for complex tasks.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>Why should I always use extended thinking mode?</summary>
      <p>Without extended thinking, AI models default to faster but shallower responses. Always-on thinking mode forces the AI to reason more carefully, producing answers that are more accurate, better structured, and less prone to errors or hallucinations. For professionals who rely on AI for critical work, this means every conversation starts with the model's best effort.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>Does think mode make AI smarter?</summary>
      <p>Think mode doesn't change the underlying AI model, but it unlocks its full reasoning potential. The same model produces significantly better results because it spends more computational effort on each response. Think of it as the difference between a quick mental estimate and carefully working through a problem on paper — same brain, much better output.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>Is there a Chrome extension to enable ChatGPT think mode automatically?</summary>
      <p>Yes — ThinkMode+ is a Chrome and Edge extension built specifically for this purpose. It automatically enables think mode on ChatGPT every time you open a new chat. It also works on Claude and Gemini, making it the only extension that covers all three major AI platforms in one install.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>How do I turn on extended thinking every time in ChatGPT?</summary>
      <p>The easiest way is to install ThinkMode+. Without it, you would need to manually click the thinking toggle every single time you start a new conversation — ChatGPT resets this setting by default. ThinkMode+ eliminates this step by automatically detecting new chats and enabling extended thinking before you even type your first message.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>What is the difference between think mode and normal mode in ChatGPT?</summary>
      <p>In normal mode, ChatGPT generates responses quickly using standard processing. In think mode, ChatGPT takes additional time to reason through your question step by step. Think mode produces longer, more detailed, and more accurate answers — especially for code, math, logic, or multi-step reasoning. The tradeoff is slightly longer response times, but the quality improvement is significant.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>Does ThinkMode+ work on Edge browser?</summary>
      <p>Yes. ThinkMode+ is fully compatible with Microsoft Edge since Edge supports Chrome extensions natively. Install ThinkMode+ from the Chrome Web Store and use it on Edge exactly the same way. All features work identically on both browsers.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>How do I install ThinkMode+?</summary>
      <p>Visit the Chrome Web Store, search for ThinkMode+, and click "Add to Chrome." The extension installs in seconds. Once installed, pin it to your toolbar, click the icon, and toggle on the platforms you want. Extended thinking will now auto-enable on every new chat across your selected platforms.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>Will ThinkMode+ slow down my browser?</summary>
      <p>No. ThinkMode+ is extremely lightweight — the entire extension is under 50KB with zero external dependencies. It only activates on supported AI platform pages and uses minimal CPU. It has zero impact on page load times or AI response speed.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="seo-faq-item">
      <summary>What AI platforms does ThinkMode+ support?</summary>
      <p>ThinkMode+ supports three major AI platforms: ChatGPT (chatgpt.com) by OpenAI, Claude (claude.ai) by Anthropic, and Gemini (gemini.google.com) by Google. Each platform can be enabled or disabled independently. Support for additional AI platforms may be added in future updates.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>
